<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-22T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-22T07:00:00-05:00" n="132" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2696</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-22T20:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My telegram August 21, 4 p.m. The President informs me that eighteen
                            provinces nave accepted the plan of a provisional National Council of
                            five members from each province which is to complete the Constitution
                            and parliamentary election law. Kwangtung, Kwangsi, Yunnan, have not yet
                            agreed but he hopes to persuade them.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>